@node "Description" ""


  Ever wished that you could change your Work Bench
  Patterns when you reboot your Amiga?

  Then you have been waiting for this program with
  Bated breath!

  The one and only function of this here program is
  to randomly change your screen, workbench, and
  window patterns every time your computer boots up.

  Several patterns have been included with PicRnd,
  in case you don't have any. I made them one winter
  morning while I was waiting for my ride to work.
  Nothing fancy, but they are free.

  Now for the standard legal mumbojumbo:

  You use this program at your own risk. The author
  can not be held liable for any damage to your
  system or loss of data from the use of this program.

  The author maintains all rights to this program.

  This program is freeware. I programmed it purely for
  the fun of programming it. As long as there is no
  charge made for the program and the archive remains
  intact, it can be distributed as far and wide as
  possible. If you like it please send a comment to
  me at:

         @{"lwulffptialaska.net" link "TheAuthor" 0}

  Otherwise, onward with the @{"installation" link "InstallIt" 0}

@endnode

@node "InstallIt" ""


  No fancy installation script here. To lazy
  to write one. You are lucky to get this
  instruction guide.

  To install:

     copy the program PicRnd to some directory
          in your path (I use c)

     Modify your startup sequence with the line:

          PicRnd (may have to make it c:PicRnd)

     This needs to go before IPrefs. Once IPrefs
     runs the selected pictures can't be changed.

     This program looks for your pictures in the:

          Sys:Prefs/Patterns drawer.

     Make sure you have some iff picture files in
     this directory, or your computer will crash
     big time.

     Now reboot your computer, open your WBPatterns
     pref editor, and change the settings to:

          Screen Picture    ScPic
          Workbench Picture WbPic
          Window Picture    WdPic

     Save your settings. And you should now be set
     up and ready to boggy. So it is time to go to
     @{"How it Works" link "UseIt" 0}


@endnode

@node "UseIt" ""


  Using this program is easy, once it is setup.

  Once set up it is automatic. It has no window,
  Icon, or interface of any kind.

  So this was sort of a useless section.

  What the program does is copy 3 random iff
  files to ScPic, WbPic, and WdPic. if this is
  done before IPrefs is loaded, these files will
  be used when IPrefs loads.


@endnode

@node "TheAuthor" ""


  What can I say about myself?

  Well I am not a programmer, in fact this was
