@endnode

@node "AHistory" ""


  This is version 1.0, so there is not much
  in the way of history.

  This version was written and compiled on a
  Lattice C 5.01 compiler that I got with my
  Amiga 3000, and have just now got around
  to using.

  As the above might indicate, this program
  was tested on an Amiga 3000 with OS 3.1.

  While I have not tried this program with
  NickPrefs on an OS 2.1 machine, I can't
  think of any reason it would not work as
  long as it was run before NickPrefs. I
  have an old Amiga 500 with OS 2.1 that I
  need to try it on one of these days.

  If and when I get around to upgrading
  this program, I have been toying with
  adding a config file that would let the
  user specify directories and file names.
  And maybe expanding it to change sounds
  also.

@endnode

